{
  "title": "Somewhere else",
  "body": [
    "​Moving.",
    "Or, moving in.",
    "I called my mom",
    "from the new place.",
    "“Celebrate that,\" she tells me.",
    "“The last box—",
    "it makes it fun.\"",
    "",
    "​She's been splitting",
    "from Dad",
    "for 30 years,",
    "and so I listen.",
    "",
    "​When I was 19",
    "she had the youngest",
    "(who is 6 now)",
    "and that day",
    "was cold.",
    "",
    "So cold",
    "that while I was in class",
    "my tire deflated,",
    "and two strangers helped me",
    "put on the spare.",
    "",
    "​It's all scratched down",
    "in a notebook I almost threw away.",
    "​That notebook sat in closets",
    "while life kept moving.",
    "",
    "I moved out",
    "after the youngest was born.",
    "Then I lived alone,",
    "and went to class,",
    "to get a job.",
    "​All to keep moving—",
    "out and in and on and up,",
    "to come back for Thanksgiving,",
    "and maybe Christmas,",
    "so I can have",
    "all that I have",
    "and remember",
    "all that I wanted",
    "in all of these places",
    "strangers will drive past",
    "on their way to somewhere else."
  ]
}